DURING THE SEARCH SEVERAL WITNESS REPORTS WERE RECEIVED IN THE AREA OF LOWER LAKE MARY. A USFS EMPLOYEE LOCATED THE SUBJECT AT THE LAKE MARY COUNTRY STORE. THE SUBJECT WAS UNINJURED AND DID NOT REQUIRE
Creator: D10213

Specify Other for How Subject(s) Were Fo: CCSO-SAR RESPONDED TO A REPORT OF A LOST FEMALE IN THE AREA OF FRY PARK. THE SUBJECT STATED THAT SHE WAS ABANDONED IN THE AREA BY FRIENDS AND WAS ATTEMPTING TO WALK OUT. SAR UNITS AND DEPUTIES INITIATED INVESTIGATION, CONTAINMENT, AND ROUTE AND LOCATION SEARCH. DPS AIR RESCUE RESPONDED TO ASSIST WITH THE SEARCH. THE SUBJECT WALKED INTO A CONTAINMENT LOCATION AND WAS DETERMINED TO BE IN GOOD CONDITION AND WAS TRANSPORTED TO HER RESIDENCE.
Creator: D10213

Specify Other for How Subject(s) Were Fo: SUBJECT FOUND BY CONTAINMENT PATROL AFTER A REPORTED WITNESS SIGHTING.
Creator: D10213

Specify Other for How Subject(s) Were Fo: SUBJECT WAS LOCATED BY CONTAINMENT PATROL. THE CHILD WAS UNINJURED AND TRANSPORTED BACK TO THE CAMP TO BE REUNITED WITH FAMILY.
Creator: D10213

Specify Other for How Subject(s) Were Fo: CCSO-SAR RESPONDED TO A REPORT OF AN OVERDUE MOTORIST ON STONEMAN LAKE ROAD. THE SUBJECT WAS LAST HEARD FROM WHEN SHE REPORTED THAT SHE WAS LOST AT 0730. SHE STATED THAT SHE HAD TURNED OFF OF I-17 ONTO STONEMAN LAKE ROAD AND WAS EN ROUTE TO THE MORMON LAKE AREA TO MEET FAMILY. AFTER REPORTING THAT SHE WAS LOST HER CELL PHONE DIED AND NO ONE WAS ABLE TO CONTACT HER AND SHE NEVER ARRIVED AS EXPECTED. A SEARCH OF STONEMAN LAKE ROAD FROM LAKE MARY ROAD TOWARD I-17 LOCATED HER ON THE ROAD IN GOOD CON
Creator: D10213

Specify Other for How Subject(s) Were Fo: SUBJECT FOUND BY NPS SEARCHERS PRIOR TO CCSO-SAR K9 ARRIVAL
Creator: D10213

How Were the Subject(s) Found?: Found by FD in vehicle near junction Switzerland trail and Gold Hill Rd; walked out to SO vehicle.
Creator: H60161

Specify Other for How Subject(s) Were Fo: CCSO-SAR RESPONDED TO A REPORT OF AN OVERDUE HUNTER IN THE AREA OF SKINNER RIDGE. THE HUNTER HAD BEEN DROPPED OFF AT 1400 AND WAS EXPECTED TO BE BACK AT THE DROP OFF POINT AT 1900 BUT DID NOT ARRIVE. CCSO PATROL DEPUTIES RESPONDED TO THE AREA TO CONDUCT INITIAL INVESTIGATION AND CONTAINMENT. DPS AIR RESCUE WAS REQUESTED TO ASSIST WITH AN AERIAL SEARCH OF THE AREA. PRIOR TO SAR ARRIVAL IN THE AREA A DEPUTY CONDUCTING CONTAINMENT LOCATED THE SUBJECT IN GOOD CONDITION.
Creator: D10213

Specify Other for How Subject(s) Were Fo: SUBJECT WAS LOCATED DURING AN AREA SEARCH OF SEGMENT 9. SHE WAS INITIALLY UNRESPONSIVE AND FACE DOWN. SEARCHERS WERE ABLE TO AROUSE HER VERBALLY AND THEN PROVIDED MEDICAL CARE.
Creator: D10213

Specify Other for How Subject(s) Were Fo: CCSO-SAR RESPONDED TO A 911 HANG-UP WHICH WAS CORRELATED TO AN OVERDUE HIKER. DURING THE RESPONSE A DEPUTY LOCATED A T-SHIRT, TRACKS, AND CELL PHONE THAT BELONGED TO THE SUBJECT. DPS AIR RESCUE ASSISTED WITH AIR SEARCH OF THE AREA. PRIOR TO SAR ARRIVAL ON SCENE THE DEPUTY LOCATED THE SUBJECT IN GOOD CONDITION.
Creator: D10213

Specify Other for How Subject(s) Were Fo: CCSO-SAR RESPONDED TO A REPORT OF AN OVERDUE HUNTER IN THE AREA OF POCKET LAKE. A SEARCH WAS INITIATED AND DPS AIR RESCUE WAS REQUESTED TO ASSIST DUE TO THE POSSIBILITY THAT THE SUBJECT HAD A LIGHT SOURCE. DPS AIR RESCUE LOCATED THE SUBJECT IN TULE CANYON, MID-FACE ON THE SIDE OF THE CANYON. A TECHNICAL RESCUE WAS CONDUCTED TO ASSIST THE SUBJECT BACK TO THE RIM WHERE HE WAS REUNITED WITH FAMILY MEMBERS.
Creator: D10213
